dataExt.exDesc: M248TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Revere that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M248Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M248OthLeg and M248Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/anf/research-and-tech/it-serv-and-support/application-serv/office-of-geographic-information-massgis/about-massgis/massgis-strategic-plan.htmll), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: For planning purposes only. The deed is the legal definition of a parcel.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: Parcel boundaries developed from City of Revere 40 scale engineer maps. Parcel identifiers developed from City of Revere 100 scale assessors tax maps. Both map sets were in good condition. Parcel GIS was brought up-to-date using historical city records and deed research in some cases. Data developed in 2009 and updated anually through December 2021.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: City of Revere, CDM Smith, MassGIS

Consts.useLimit: This data may be appropriate for planning purposes. It should not be utilized where legal and surveyed property boundaries are required.
